name: float_f32_max_finite
description: |
  This is the largest finite binary32 value. Operations that round above this
  range may produce positive infinity, saturate, trap, or be evaluated at a
  wider precision before rounding. Pairing it with infinity targets overflow
  checks that rely on ordinary finite comparisons.
format: hex
decode-as: f32
pair:
  - with: positive-infinity.input
    hint: tricky
tags:
  - "float"
  - "floating-point"
  - "ieee-754"
  - "f32"
  - "overflow"
  - "boundary"
---
ff ff 7f 7f # 0x7f7fffff: maximum finite binary32
